title: The thousand and one nights 3 Volumes
description:
The thousand and one nights 3 Volumes - -nelly-
                 ===============================================



The thousand and one nights, Vol. 1, called in England, The Arabian nights' entertainments, in three volumes.
A new translation from the Arabic, with copious notes by Edward William Lane, author of "The modern Egyptions".
Illustrated by many hundred engravings on wood from original designs by William Harvey.
Edited by his nephew, Edward Stanley Poole.

Translation from Arabic: Edward William Lane
Edited by: Edward Stanley Poole
Title: The thousand and one nights. Vol. 1.
Publisher: London: Routledge, Warne and Routledge
Year: 1865
Format: PDF
